k.html|archivedate=2010-03-26}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Triple jump]]\n|13.28 m\n|[[Taneisha Scanlon]]\n|12 February 2005\n|\n|{{flagicon|UK}} [[Sheffield]], United Kingdom\n|\n|-\n|[[Shot put]]\n|17.06 m <ref>outdoor mark ratified as absolute record</ref>\n|[[Marita Walton]]\n|26 February 1982\n|\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[New York City]], United States\n|\n|-style=\"background:#f6F5CE;\"\n|[[Weight throw]]\n|18.66 m A\n|[[Aloife Hickey]]\n|6 February 2015\n|New Mexico Classic\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Albuquerque Convention Center|Albuquerque]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Weight Throw Results|url=http://www.directathletics.com/results/track/36437_2331630.html|publisher=directathletics.com|date=6 February 2015|accessdate=17 February 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Discus throw]]\n|47.24 m\n|[[Clare Fitgerald]]\n|10 March 2012\n|World Indoor Throwing\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[V\u00e4xj\u00f6]], Sweden\n|<ref>{{cite news|title=World Indoor Throwing 2012 Complete Results |url=http://www.worldindoorthrowing.com/pdf/WIT_2012_res.pdf |publisher=www.worldindoorthrowing.com |date=11 March 2012 |accessdate=5 April 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Women's pentathlon|Pentathlon]]\n|4214 pts\n|[[Kate O'Connor (athlete)|Kate O'Connor]]\n|27 January 2019\n|Welsh International Combined Events Championships \n|[[Cardiff]], United Kingdom\n|<ref>{{cite news|title=Kate O'Connor: Dundalk athlete regains Irish Indoor Pentathlon record in Cardiff|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/athletics/47023860|website=bbc.co.uk|date=27 January 2019|accessdate=28 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|colspan=5|{{Women's Indoor Pentathlon Score|9.02|1.74 m|12.77 m|5.94 m|2:17.22}}\n|\n|-bgcolor=#CEF6F5\n|4230 pts\n|[[Grace McKenzie (athlete)|Grace McKenzie]]\n|8 March 2019\n|[[2019 NCAA Division I Indoor Track and Field Championships|NCAA Division I Championships]] \n|[[Birmingham, Alabama|Birmingham]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=2019 NCAA Division I Indoor