 from Elche]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Valencian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Elche CF Ilicitano footballers]]\n[[Category:Elche CF players]]\n[[Category:Villajoyosa CF footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Barcelona B players]]\n[[Category:Orihuela CF players]]\n[[Category:UE Lleida players]]\n[[Category:Super League Greece players]]\n[[Category:Asteras Tripoli F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Israeli Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Maccabi Haifa F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 2 players]]\n[[Category:FC Sochaux-Montb\u00e9liard players]]\n[[Category:Cypriot First Division players]]\n[[Category:Anorthosis Famagusta FC players]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Israel]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Greece]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Israel]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in France]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Cyprus]]\n", "text_old": "{{spanish name 2|Rayos|Serna}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Rayo\n| image = MHFC-Ruben-Rayos.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Rayos as a [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]] player (2013)\n| fullname = Rub\u00e9n Rayos Serna\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1986|6|21|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Elche]], [[Spain]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.76}}\n| position = [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|Attacking midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Anorthosis Famagusta FC|Anorthosis]]\n| clubnumber = 10\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 = [[Elche CF|Elche]]\n| years1 = 2005\u20132006\n| years2 = 2006\u20132008\n| years3 = 2006\u20132008\n| years4 = 2008\u20132009\n| years5 = 2009\u20132010\n| years6 = 2010\u20132011\n| years7 = 2011\u20132013\n| years8 = 2013\u20132015\n| years9 = 2015\u20132016\n| years10 = 2016\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Elche CF Ilicitano|Elche B]]\n| clubs2 = [[Elche CF|Elche]]\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Villajoyosa CF|Villajoyosa]] (loan)\n| clubs4 = [[FC Barcelona B|Barcelona B]]\n| clubs5 = [[Orihuela CF|Orihuela]]\n| clubs6 = [[UE Lleida|Lleida]]\n| clubs7 = [[Asteras Tripoli F.C.|Asteras Tripoli]]\n| clubs8 = [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]]\n| clubs9 = [[FC Sochaux-Montb\u00e9liard|Sochaux]]\n| clubs10 = [[Anorthosis Famagusta FC|Anorthosis]]\n| caps1 =\n| caps2 = 0\n| caps3 = 62\n| caps4 = 23\n| caps5 = 35\n| caps6 = 33\n| caps7 = 62\n| caps8 = 54\n| caps9 = 12\n| caps10 = 111\n| totalcaps = \n| goals1 =\n| goals2 = 0\n| goals3 = 20\n| goals4 = 0\n| goals5 = 11\n| goals6 = 19\n| goals7 = 12\n| goals8 = 17\n| goals9 = 0\n| goals10 = 30\n| totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 =\n| nationalteam1 =\n| nationalcaps1 =\n| nationalgoals1 =\n| club-update = 9 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update =\n}}\n'''Rub\u00e9n Rayos Serna''' (born 21 June 1986), commonly known as '''Rayo''', is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for Cypriot club [[Anorthosis Famagusta FC]].\n\n==Club career==\nRayo was born in [[Elche]], [[Valencian Community]]. He finished his formation with local [[Elche CF]], and played only [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]] football until the age of 25, representing [[Villajoyosa CF]], [[FC Barcelona B]],<ref>{{cite web | url = http://mundoblaugrana.wordpress.com/2008/07/11/ruben-rayos-primer-fichaje-del-barcelona-atletic/ | title = Rub\u00e9n Rayos, primer fichaje del Barcelona Atletic | trans-title = Rub\u00e9n Rayos, first Barcelona Atletic signing | publisher = Mundo Blaugrana | language = es | date = 11 July 2008 | accessdate = 26 July 2013}}</ref> [[Orihuela CF]]<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.laverdad.es/alicante/20090826/deportes_alicante/orihuela/orihuela-refuerza-plantilla-jugadores-20090826.html | title = El Orihuela refuerza la plantilla con jugadores de las canteras del Barcelona, Espa\u00f1ol y H\u00e9rcules | trans-title = Orihuela strengthen squad with players from Barcelona, Espa\u00f1ol and H\u00e9rcules youth systems | newspaper = [[La Verdad (Murcia)|La Verdad]] | language = es | date = 26 August 2009 | accessdate = 26 July 2013}}</ref> and [[UE Lleida]].<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.lacronicadeleon.es/2011/05/20/deportes/mayor-avala-al-goleador-rayos-118974.htm | title = M\u00e1yor avala al goleador Rayos | trans-title = M\u00e1yor gives thumbs up to scorer Rayos | newspaper = La Cr\u00f3nica de Le\u00f3n | language = es | date = 20 May 2011 | accessdate = 26 July 2013 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111222164317/http://www.lacronicadeleon.es/2011/05/20/deportes/mayor-avala-al-goleador-rayos-118974.htm | archivedate = 22 December 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn the summer of 2011, Rayo moved straight into the [[Superleague Greece]], joining a host of compatriots at [[Asteras Tripoli F.C.|Asteras Tripoli FC]]. He scored five league goals in [[2011\u201312 Superleague Greece|his first season]], adding three in [[2011\u201312 Greek Football Cup|the campaign]]'s [[Greek Football Cup|domestic cup]].\n\nIn [[2012\u201313 Superleague Greece|2012\u201313]], Rayo improved his overall totals to nine goals and 12 [[Assist (football)|assists]]. In [[2012\u201313 Greek Football Cup|the final of the Greek Cup]], against [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos FC]], he put his team ahead 1\u20130, but in an eventual 1\u20133 [[Overtime (sports)|extra time]] loss;<ref>{{cite news | url = http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2013/05/11/internacional/1368304144_022257.html | title = El Olympiacos de M\u00edchel logra el doblete tras ganar la Copa | trans-title = M\u00edchel's Olympiacos get double after Cup win | newspaper = [[Diario AS]] | language = es | date = 12 May 2013 | accessdate = 26 July 2013}}</ref> he was eventually chosen Best Foreign Player for his exploits<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.marca.com/2014/02/05/futbol/futbol_internacional/espanoles_mundo/1391615827.html | title = Rub\u00e9n Rayos, mejor extranjero de la pasada liga griega | trans-title = Rub\u00e9n Rayos, best foreign in last Greek league | newspaper = [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] | language = es | date = 5 February 2014 | accessdate = 1 October 2014}}</ref> and, during most of his spell in [[Greece]], was also [[Captain (association football)|club captain]].\n\nOn 6 June 2013, Rayo signed a three-year contract with [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa FC]], netting 11 goals in 27 appearances in [[2013\u201314 Israeli Premier League|his first year]] to help his new team to the fourth position in the regular season of the [[Israeli Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://eng.football.org.il/Leagues/Pages/PlayerTopGoals.aspx?LEAGUE_ID=40&SEASON_ID=15 | title = Leading goalscorer | publisher = [[Israel Football Association]] | accessdate = 1 October 2014}}</ref> However, in March 2014, he was involved in an incident with [[Bnei Yehuda Tel Aviv F.C.]]'s [[Rafi Dahan]], his harsh tackle producing an [[anterior cruciate ligament]] injury to his opponent which sidelined him for almost one year \u2013 he received a straight [[Ejection (sports)|red card]] for his action,<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.marca.com/2014/03/11/futbol/futbol_internacional/espanoles_mundo/1394554085.html | title = La brutal entrada de Rub\u00e9n Rayos | trans-title = Rub\u00e9n Rayos' brutal tackle | newspaper = Marca | language = es | date = 11 March 2014 | accessdate = 1 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.elmundo.es/deportes/2014/03/11/531f54b2e2704eb7078b4583.html | title = Piden sanci\u00f3n ejemplar para la brutal entrada de Rayos | trans-title = Exemplary sanction wanted for Rayos' brutal tackle | newspaper = [[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]] | language = es | date = 11 March 2014 | accessdate = 1 October 2014}}</ref> and Dahan was eventually forced to retire;<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/rafi-dahan-forced-retire-aged-25-result-ruben-rayos-tackle-video/ | title = Rafi Dahan forced to retire aged just 25 as a result of THAT Rub\u00e9n Rayos tackle | publisher = 101 Great Goals | date = 6 March 2015 | accessdate = 22 June 2015}}</ref> following his retirement, Dahan filed a [[lawsuit]] against Rayo and Maccabi Haifa in an Israeli court.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.sport5.co.il/HTML/Articles/Article.64.327541.html| title =  \u05de\u05d9\u05dc\u05d9\u05d5\u05df \u05e9\u05e7\u05dc\u05d9\u05dd: \u05ea\u05d1\u05d9\u05e2\u05ea \u05d4\u05e2\u05e0\u05e7 \u05d1\u05ea\u05d9\u05e7 \u05e8\u05e4\u05d9 \u05d3\u05d4\u05df \u2013 \u05e8\u05d0\u05d9\u05d5\u05e1 21 | trans-title = Twenty-one million NIS: The big lawsuit in the Dahan \u2013 Rayos case | publisher = [[Sport 5]] | language = he | date = 7 November 2019 | accessdate = 7 November 2019}}</ref>. Dahan won the lawsuit against Rayo and Maccabi Haifa, the judge ruling that Rayo's actions were deliberate.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.haaretz.co.il/sport/israel-soccer/1.8333657 | title = \u05d7\u05e8\u05d9\u05d2 \u05d5\u05e0\u05e2\u05e9\u05d4 \u05d1\u05de\u05db\u05d5\u05d5\u05df : \u05d1\u05d9\u05ea \u05d4\u05de\u05e9\u05e4\u05d8 \u05d4\u05d5\u05e8\u05d4 \u05dc\u05e8\u05d0\u05d9\u05d5\u05e1 \u05d5\u05de\u05db\u05d1\u05d9 \u05d7\u05d9\u05e4\u05d4 \u05dc\u05e9\u05dc\u05dd \u05de\u05d9\u05dc\u05d5\u05e0\u05d9\u05dd \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05e7\u05df \u05e9\u05e4\u05e6\u05e2 \u05d1\u05de\u05e9\u05d7\u05e7 | trans-title = Exceptional and Deliberate: The court orders Rayos and Maccabi Haifa to pay millions to an injured player | publisher = [[Haaretz]] | language = he | date = 30 December 2019 | accessdate = 30 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 July 2015, Rayo joined French side [[FC Sochaux-Montb\u00e9liard]], signing a two-year deal for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Ruben-rayos-a-sochaux-off/572871| title = Ruben Rayos \u00e0 Sochaux (off.) | trans-title = Ruben Rayos to Sochaux (off.) | newspaper = [[L'\u00c9quipe]] | language = fr | date = 8 July 2015 | accessdate = 14 July 2015}}</ref> Roughly one year later, he moved to [[Anorthosis Famagusta FC]] in the [[Cypriot First Division]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.anorthosisfc.com.cy/2016/07/apoktisi-ruben-rayos-serna/| title = \u0391\u03c0\u03cc\u03ba\u03c4\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7 Ruben Rayos Serna | trans-title = Acquisition of Ruben Rayos Serna | publisher = Anorthosis Famagusta | language = el | date = 14 July 2016 | accessdate = 14 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|9 March 2020}}<ref>{{Soccerway|ruben-rayos-serna/62797}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Club\n! rowspan=2 | Season\n! colspan=3 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | Continental\n! colspan=2 | Other\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Division\n! Apps\n! Goals\n! Apps\n! Goals\n! Apps\n! Goals\n! Apps\n! Goals\n! Apps\n! Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Asteras Tripoli F.C.|Asteras Tripoli]]\n|[[2011-12 Superleague Greece|2011\u201312]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Superleague Greece|Superleague]]\n|27||5||4||3||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||31||8\n|-\n|[[2012-13 Superleague Greece|2012\u201313]]\n|35||7||9||2||4||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||48||10\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!62!!12!!13!!5!!4!!1!!0!!0!!79!!18\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]]\n|[[2013-14 Israeli Premier League|2013\u201314]]\n|rowspan=2|[[Israeli Premier League]]\n|27||11||1||0||12||6||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||40||17\n|-\n|[[2014-15 Israeli Premier League|2014\u201315]]\n|27||6||2||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||6||4||35||12\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!54!!17!!3!!2!!12!!6!!6!!4!!75!!29\n|-\n|[[FC Sochaux-Montb\u00e9liard|Sochaux]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Ligue 2|2015\u201316]]\n|[[Ligue 2]]\n|12||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2||0||16||0\n|-\n|rowspan=5|[[Anorthosis Famagusta FC|Anorthosis]]\n|[[2016-17 Cypriot First Division|2016\u201317]]\n|rowspan=4|[[Cypriot First Division]]\n|30||8||4||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||34||10\n|-\n|[[2017-18 Cypriot First Division|2017\u201318]]\n|34||5||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||36||5\n|-\n|[[2018-19 Cypriot First Division|2018\u201319]]\n|24||3||2||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||28||3\n|-\n|[[2019-20 Cypriot First Division|2019\u201320]]\n|23||14||2||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||25||15\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!111!!30!!10!!3!!2!!0!!0!!0!!123!!33\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!239!!59!!28!!10!!18!!7!!8!!4!!293!!80\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Asteras Tripoli'''\n*[[Greek Football Cup]] runner-up: [[2012\u201313 Greek Football Cup|2012\u201313]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Superleague Greece]] Player of the Year: [[2012\u201313 Superleague Greece|2012\u201313]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|300054}}\n\n{{Anorthosis Famagusta FC squad}}\n{{Super League Greece foreigner of the year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rayos, Ruben}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Elche]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Valencian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Elche CF Ilicitano footballers]]\n[[Category:Elche CF players]]\n[[Category:Villajoyosa CF footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Barcelona B players]]\n[[Category:Orihuela CF players]]\n[[Category:UE Lleida players]]\n[[Category:Super League Greece players]]\n[[Category:Asteras Tripoli F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Israeli Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Maccabi Haifa F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 2 players]]\n[[Category:FC Sochaux-Montb\u00e9liard players]]\n[[Category:Cypriot First Division players]]\n[[Category:Anorthosis Famagusta FC players]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[